				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">I agree.  To me a hero is someone that did above and beyond the call of duty in the situation.   To me, her situation is like that of Scott O'Grady.  He survived a very hard time, but did nothing above and beyond..IMHO.
<br />

<br />
A real hero is someone like JFK (before he entered politics) when he was rammed in his PT boat.  <a href="http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2002/11/1120_021120_kennedy_pt_109.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">He actually had to drag some of his men by his teeth while he swam to several islands attempting to find food/water/safety.</a>  All with a seriously injured back.  He did not have to do this but he managed to do it to save their lives.  That is a big difference.<span class="gensmall"></span>


