				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">Is she a hero?
<br />

<br />
Of course she is and so is every service member in Iraq now and before.  She was the spotlight as the US government displayed its ability to recover prisoners unopposed in the middle of Baghdad.  She got the spotlight. I don't think she asked for it.  She did suffer for it.
<br />

<br />
I think everyone there and even those stationed elsewhere as support deserves our appreciation for the sacrifices those soldiers are making.  Just going abroad to fight a war is the work of a hero. Being put in the media doesnt make you any less of one.  I imagine that she is still sacrificing and will continue to do so all of her life... considering the extent of the injuries she sustained.<span class="gensmall"></span>


