				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">There must be a lot of Iraqi heroes out there then Poppa.  The word here is bandied around so much that it loses any sense.  Superman was a hero, Spiderman was a hero, some chich who got caught while driving a car is a prisoner.
<br />

<br />
Being that the prisoner was a female got people's emotions going.  Western countries don't typically put females (or children) at risk even in times of war.  When a female is caught it brings out the Western man's protective nature.
<br />

<br />
I'd agree with other posters that the only true heroic deeds were done by the men who saved her.  It wasn't logical to risk all those people to save one person but since it was a woman in trouble the logic gave way to emotion and I'd imagine a lot of men volunteered or were chomping at the bit to go and rescue her.  If there was only one hero in this entire thing it'd be the person who ordered her rescue.<span class="gensmall"></span>


